{"type":"message","id":"8b0d1f6a","parentId":"1cf98fdf","timestamp":"2026-03-06T02:08:53.407Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the results:\n\n1. **Gateway:** The gateway is running (RPC probe: ok, Listening: *:18789), but the LaunchAgent service is not loaded. This means the gateway is running but not as a proper service. This might be okay if it was started manually, but it's not ideal.\n\n2. **Parse:** HTTP 200 ✓\n3. **LLM Survivor:** HTTP 200 ✓\n4. **Subagents:** No active or recent subagents in last 30 minutes\n5. **Tasks:** No pending task files found\n\nThe gateway situation is a bit concerning - it's running but not as a proper service. However, the RPC probe is OK, so it's functional.\n\nLet me check for any critical escalations or blocked items. I should also check if there are any tasks in the Neo4j database or any other signals.\n\nActually, looking at the heartbeat checklist again:\n- Gateway: running (RPC probe ok) ✓\n- Parse: 200 ✓\n- LLM Survivor: 200 ✓\n- Subagents: none stuck ✓\n- No pending tasks found\n\nThe only minor issue is that the gateway service is not properly installed/loaded, but it's running. This isn't critical - the gateway is functional.\n\nFor the Self-Direction section:\n- No new signals/tasks/escalations\n- Nothing urgent to act on\n- No proactive action needed right now\n\nSince nothing needs attention, I should respond with HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nWait, I should also check if there's anything in the agents' memory files or any escalations from Ögedei. Let me quickly check for any escalation files or critical flags.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check for any critical escalations or blocked agents:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4675b0d5851140289a6cf1ce","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/*/escalation* ~/.openclaw/agents/*/blocked* 2>/dev/null || echo \"No escalation/blocked files\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c9848159bf09